@fastLLM text
Use fastLLM for cheap short-form language work: extraction, normalization, lightweight synthesis, simple classification, and quick answers where latency matters.
Prefer it when the step is language-heavy but shallow enough that exactness does not depend on deeper reasoning or deterministic computation.
Good fits include small label extraction, concise rewrites, short summaries, and lightweight comparisons over already obvious evidence.
Avoid fastLLM for planning, mathematical proof, search over state spaces, delicate policy evaluation, or answers that must preserve an exact requested structure from computed results.
